Class SAFSCommands

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.SAFSPlus
      • org.safs.selenium.webdriver.SeleniumPlus
        • org.safs.cukes.ai.selenium.SAFSCommands

  • public class SAFSCommands
extends SeleniumPlus
    Prerequisite
    A SeleniumPlus test has properly started.

    Purpose
    This class is used to handle the "safs driver command" step definitions for gherkin feature files.

      • runDriverCommand

        @Then(value="do safs command {string}")
public TestRecordHelper runDriverCommand(java.lang.String command)
                                                                           throws java.lang.Throwable
        Run a SAFS Driver Command. The safs command takes no parameters. This method performs SAFS Expression processing on all input parameters.

        Cucumber Expression: "do safs command {string}"
        {string} Matches single-quoted or double-quoted strings, for example "banana split" or 'banana split' (but not banana split).

        Example Scenario Step:

          Then do safs command "ClearClipboard"
        Parameters:
        command - The DriverCommand keyword (command) to perform
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable

      • runDriverCommand

        @Then(value="do safs command {string} using {list}")
public TestRecordHelper runDriverCommand(java.lang.String command,
                                                                                               java.util.List<java.lang.String> parameters)
                                                                                        throws java.lang.Throwable
        Run a SAFS Driver Command. The safs command may take one or more parameters. This method performs SAFS Expression processing on all input parameters.

        Cucumber Expression: "do safs command {string} using {list}
        {string} Matches single-quoted or double-quoted strings, for example "banana split" or 'banana split' (but not banana split).
        {list} Represents a list of string parameters, the parameters can be delimited by TestRecordData.POSSIBLE_SEPARATOR.

        Example Scenario Step:

          Then do safs command "GetAppMapValue" using " , ApplicationConstants, WebURL, varURL"
          Then do safs command "GetAppMapValue" using " $ ApplicationConstants$ WebURL$ varURL"
        Parameters:
        command - The DriverCommand keyword (command) to perform
        parameters - List<String> of parameters used by the command. Can be null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
